AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:IdentifiedObject
AFElementTemplate.Description: This is a root class to provide common naming attributes for all classes needing naming attributes

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.aliasName
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.description
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.localName
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The localName is a human readable name of the object. It is only used with objects organized in a naming hierarchy. The simplest naming hierarchy has just one parent (the root) giving a flat naming hierarchy. However, the naming hierarchy usually has several levels, e.g. Substation, VoltageLevel, Equipment etc. Children of the same parent have names that are unique among them. If the uniqueness requirement cannot be met IdentifiedObject.localName shall not be used, use IdentifiedObject.name instead.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: IdentifiedObject.name
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The name is a free text human readable name of the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:PowerSystemResource
AFElementTemplate.Description: A power system resource can be an item of equipment such as a Switch, an EquipmentContainer containing many individual items of equipment such as a Substation, or an organisational entity such as Company or SubControlArea. This provides for the nesting of collections of PowerSystemResources within other PowerSystemResources. For example, a Switch could be a member of a Substation and a Substation could be a member of a division of a Company.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PowerSystemResource.Contains_Measurements
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The Measurements that are included in the naming hierarchy where the PSR is the containing object

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Equipment
AFElementTemplate.Description: The parts of a power system that are physical devices, electronic or mechanical

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:ConductingEquipment
AFElementTemplate.Description: The parts of the power system that are designed to carry current or that are conductively connected therewith. ConductingEquipment is contained within an EquipmentContainer that may be a Substation, or a VoltageLevel or a Bay within a Substation.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Conductor
AFElementTemplate.Description: Combination of conducting material with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry current between points in the power system.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.b0ch
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.bch
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.g0ch
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.gch
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.length
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Segment length for calculating line section capabilities

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.r
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.r0
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.x
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Conductor.x0
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:ACLineSegment
AFElementTemplate.Description: A wire or combination of wires, with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry alternating current between points in the power system.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:BasePower
AFElementTemplate.Description: The BasePower class defines the base power used in the per unit calculations.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BasePower.basePower
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Definition of base power.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:BaseVoltage
AFElementTemplate.Description: Collection of BaseVoltages which is used to verify that the BusbarSection.BaseVoltage and other voltage attributes in the CIM are given a value existing in the collection.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: BaseVoltage.nominalVoltage
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The PowerSystemResource's base voltage.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:EquipmentContainer
AFElementTemplate.Description: A modeling construct to provide a root class for all Equipment classes

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Bay
AFElementTemplate.Description: A collection of power system resources (within a given substation) including conducting equipment, protection relays, measurements, and telemetry.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Bay.bayEnergyMeasFlag
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Indicates the presence/absence of energy measurements.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Bay.bayPowerMeasFlag
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Indicates the presence/absence of active/reactive power measurements.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Bay.MemberOf_Substation
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The association is used in the naming hierarchy.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Bay.MemberOf_VoltageLevel
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The association is used in the naming hierarchy.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Switch
AFElementTemplate.Description: A generic device designed to close, or open, or both, one or more electric circuits.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Switch.normalOpen
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The attribute is used in cases when no Measurement for the status value is present. If the Switch has a status measurment the Discrete.normalValue is expected to match with the Switch.normalOpen.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Switch.retained
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Branch is retained in a bus branch model.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Switch.switchOnCount
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The switch on count since the switch was last reset or initialized.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Switch.switchOnDate
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The date and time when the switch was last switched on.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Breaker
AFElementTemplate.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal circuit conditions and also making, carrying for a specified time, and breaking currents under specified abnormal circuit conditions e.g. those of short circuit.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Breaker.inTransitTime
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The transition time from open to close.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Breaker.ratedCurrent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fault interrupting current rating.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Connector
AFElementTemplate.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation and are modelled with a single logical terminal.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:BusbarSection
AFElementTemplate.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation. Voltage measurements are typically obtained from VoltageTransformers that are connected to busbar sections. A bus bar section may have many physical terminals but for analysis is modelled with exactly one logical terminal.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Company
AFElementTemplate.Description: A company is a legal entity that owns and operates power system resources and is a party to interchange and transmission contracts.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Company.Operates_PSRs
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: PowerSystemResources the Company operates.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:CompositeSwitch
AFElementTemplate.Description: A model of a set of individual Switches normally enclosed within the same cabinet and possibly with interlocks that restrict the combination of switch positions. These are typically found in medium voltage distribution networks. A CompositeSwitch could represent a Ring-Main-Unit (RMU), or pad-mounted switchgear, with primitive internal devices such as an internal bus-bar plus 3 or 4 internal switches each of which may individually be open or closed. A CompositeSwitch and a set of contained Switches can also be used to represent a multi-position switch e.g. a switch that can connect a circuit to Ground, Open or Busbar.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: CompositeSwitch.compositeSwitchType
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: An alphanumeric code that can be used as a reference to extar information such as the description of the interlocking scheme if any

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Control
AFElementTemplate.Description: Control is used for supervisory/device control. It represents control outputs that are used to change the state in a process, e.g. close or open breaker, a set point value or a raise lower command.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:DCLineSegment
AFElementTemplate.Description: A wire or combination of wires not insulated from one another, with consistent electrical characteristics, used to carry direct current between points in the DC region of the power system.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: DCLineSegment.dcSegmentInductance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Inductance of the DC line segment.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: DCLineSegment.dcSegmentResistance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Resistance of the DC line segment.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Disconnector
AFElementTemplate.Description: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for changing the connections in a circuit, or for isolating a circuit or equipment from a source of power. It is required to open or close circuits when negligible current is broken or made.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:EnergyConsumer
AFElementTemplate.Description: Generic user of energy - a point of consumption on the power system model

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.customerCount
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Number of individual customers represented by this Demand

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.pfixed
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.pfixedPct
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fixed active power as per cent of load group fixed active power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.qfixed
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: EnergyConsumer.qfixedPct
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fixed reactive power as per cent of load group fixed reactive power.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Fuse
AFElementTemplate.Description: An overcurrent protective device with a circuit opening fusible part that is heated and severed by the passage of overcurrent through it. A fuse is considered a switching device because it breaks current.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: Fuse.ampRating
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Fault interrupting current rating.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:GeographicalRegion
AFElementTemplate.Description: A geographical region of a power system network model.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: GeographicalRegion.Regions
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The association is used in the naming hierarchy.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Ground
AFElementTemplate.Description: A common point for connecting grounded conducting equipment such as shunt capacitors. The power system model can have more than one ground.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:GroundDisconnector
AFElementTemplate.Description: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for isolating a circuit or equipment from Ground.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Jumper
AFElementTemplate.Description: A short section of conductor with negligible impedance which can be manually removed and replaced if the circuit is de-energized. Note that zero-impedance branches can be modelled by an ACLineSegment with a zero impedance ConductorType

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Junction
AFElementTemplate.Description: A point where one or more conducting equipments are connected with zero resistance.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Line
AFElementTemplate.Description: A component part of a system extending between adjacent substations or from a substation to an adjacent interconnection point.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:LoadBreakSwitch
AFElementTemplate.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal operating conditions.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: LoadBreakSwitch.ratedCurrent
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Current carrying capacity of a wire or cable under stated thermal conditions.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:Measurement
AFElementTemplate.Description: A Measurement represents any measured, calculated or non-measured non-calculated quantity. Any piece of equipment may contain Measurements, e.g. a substation may have temperature measurements and door open indications, a transformer may have oil temperature and tank pressure measurements, a bay may contain a number of power flow measurements and a Breaker may contain a switch status measurement. The PSR - Measurement association is intended to capture this use of Measurement and is included in the naming hierarchy based on EquipmentContainer. The naming hierarchy typically has Measurements as leafs, e.g. Substation-VoltageLevel-Bay-Switch-Measurement. Some Measurements represent quantities related to a particular sensor location in the network, e.g. a voltage transformer (PT) at a busbar or a current transformer (CT) at the bar between a breaker and an isolator. The sensing position is not captured in the PSR - Measurement association. Instead it is captured by the Measurement - Te

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:PowerTransformer
AFElementTemplate.Description: An electrical device consisting of two or more coupled windings, with or without a magnetic core, for introducing mutual coupling between electric circuits. Transformers can be used to control voltage and phase shift (active power flow).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PowerTransformer.bmagSat
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Core shunt magnetizing susceptance in the saturation region.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PowerTransformer.magBaseU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The reference voltage at which the magnetizing saturation measurements were made

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: PowerTransformer.magSatFlux
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Core magnetizing saturation curve knee flux level.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:RectifierInverter
AFElementTemplate.Description: Bi-directional AC-DC conversion equipment that can be used to control DC current, DC voltage, DC power flow, or firing angle.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.bridges
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Number of bridges

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.commutatingReactance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Commutating reactance at AC bus frequency.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.commutatingResistance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Commutating resistance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.compoundResistance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Compounding resistance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.frequency
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Frequency on the AC side.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.maxP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The maximum active power on the DC side at which the fconverter should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.maxU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The maximum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.minCompoundVoltage
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Minimum compounded DC voltage

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.minP
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The minimum active power on the DC side at which the converter should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.minU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The minimum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.operatingMode
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Operating mode for the converter.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RectifierInverter.ratedU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Rectifier/inverter primary base voltage

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:RegulatingCondEq
AFElementTemplate.Description: RegulatingCondEq is a type of ConductingEquipment that can regulate Measurements and have a RegulationSchedule.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: RegulatingCondEq.Controls
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The controller outputs used to actually govern a regulating device, e.g. the magnetization of a synchronous machine or capacitor bank breaker actuator.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:SeriesCompensator
AFElementTemplate.Description: A Series Compensator is a series capacitor or reactor or an AC transmission line without charging susceptance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: SeriesCompensator.r
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence resistance.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: SeriesCompensator.x
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence reactance.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:ServiceDeliveryPoint
AFElementTemplate.Description: There can be multiple service points at a single ServiceLocation, each one identified as a ServiceDeliveryPoint. They deliver service in accordance with a CustomerAgreement. A service point exists within a ServiceLocation and is used at the place where a meter may be installed. Properties include: 1) serviceType (gas, electric, water) 2) servicePhase 3) voltageLevel 4) vtdtReference (optional, where meters are indirectly connected for a medium voltage service).

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:ShuntCompensator
AFElementTemplate.Description: A shunt capacitor or reactor or switchable bank of shunt capacitors or reactors. A section of a shunt compensator is an individual capacitor or reactor. Negative values for mVArPerSection and nominalMVAr indicate that the compensator is a reactor.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.aVRDelay
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Time delay required for the device to be connected or disconnected by automatic voltage regulation (AVR).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.impedance
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The positive sequence impedance of the capacitor.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.maximumSections
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For a capacitor bank, the maximum number of sections that may be switched in.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.maxU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The maximum voltage at which the capacitor bank should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.minU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The minimum voltage at which the capacitor bank should operate.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.nomQ
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Nominal reactive power output of the capacitor bank at the nominal voltage. This number should be positive.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.nomU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The nominal voltage at which the nominal reactive power was measured. This should normally be within 10% of the voltage at which the capacitor is connected to the network.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.normalSections
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For a capacitor bank, the normal number of sections switched in. This number should correspond to the nominal reactive power (nomQ).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.reactivePerSection
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For a capacitor bank, the size in reactive power of each switchable section at the nominal voltage.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.switchOnCount
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The switch on count since the capacitor count was last reset or initialized.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.switchOnDate
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The date and time when the capacitor bank was last switched on.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.voltageSensitivity
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Voltage sensitivity required for the device to regulate the bus voltage, in voltage/reactive power.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: ShuntCompensator.yPerSection
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For a capacitor bank, the admittance of each switchable section. Calculated using the reactive power per section and corrected for network voltage.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:StaticVarCompensator
AFElementTemplate.Description: A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms. The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.capacitiveRating
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Maximum available capacitive reactive power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.inductiveRating
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Maximum available inductive reactive power

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.slope
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The characteristics slope of an SVC defines how the reactive power output changes in proportion to the difference between the regulated bus voltage and the voltage setpoint.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: StaticVarCompensator.voltageSetPoint
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The reactive power output of the SVC is proportional to the difference between the voltage at the regulated bus and the voltage setpoint. When the regulated bus voltage is equal to the voltage setpoint, the reactive power output is zero.

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:TapChanger

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.initialDelay
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For an LTC, the delay for initial tap changer operation (first step change)

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.lowStep
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Lowest possible tap step position, retard from neutral

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.neutralStep

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.neutralU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Voltage at which the winding operates at the neutral tap setting.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.normalStep
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The tap step position used in "normal" network operation for this winding. For a "Fixed" tap changer indicates the current physical tap setting.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.stepPhaseShiftIncrement
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Phase shift per step position. A positive value indicates a positive phase shift from the winding where the tap is located to the other winding (for a two-winding transformer).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.stepVoltageIncrement
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Tap step increment, in per cent of nominal voltage, per step position.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.subsequentDelay
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: For an LTC, the delay for subsequent tap changer operation (second and later step changes)

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TapChanger.TransformerWinding
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: A transformer winding may have tap changers, separately for voltage and phase angle

AFElementTemplate.Description: An electrical connection point to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called "connectivity nodes".

AFElementTemplate.Name: containership:TransformerWinding

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.b
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Magnetizing branch susceptance (B mag).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.connectionType
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The type of connection of the winding.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.emergencyS
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The apparent power that the winding can carry under emergency conditions.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.g
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Magnetizing branch conductance (G mag).

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.grounded

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.insulationU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Basic insulation level voltage rating

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.r
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series resistance of the winding.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.r0
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence series resistance of the winding.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.ratedS
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The normal apparent power rating for the winding

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.ratedU
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: The rated voltage (phase-to-phase) of the winding, usually the same as the neutral voltage.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.rground
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Ground resistance path through connected grounding transformer.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.shortTermS
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Apparent power that the winding can carry for a short period of time.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.x
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Positive sequence series reactance of the winding.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.x0
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Zero sequence series reactance of the winding.

AFAttributeTemplate.Name: TransformerWinding.xground
AFAttributeTemplate.Description: Ground reactance path through connected grounding transformer.

AFElement.Name: ACLineSegment
AFElement.Description: A wire or combination of wires, with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry alternating current between points in the power system.

AFElement.Name: BasePower
AFElement.Description: The BasePower class defines the base power used in the per unit calculations.

AFElement.Name: BaseVoltage

AFElement.Name: Bay
AFElement.Description: A collection of power system resources (within a given substation) including conducting equipment, protection relays, measurements, and telemetry.

AFElement.Name: Breaker
AFElement.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal circuit conditions and also making, carrying for a specified time, and breaking currents under specified abnormal circuit conditions e.g. those of short circuit.

AFElement.Name: BusbarSection
AFElement.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation. Voltage measurements are typically obtained from VoltageTransformers that are connected to busbar sections. A bus bar section may have many physical terminals but for analysis is modelled with exactly one logical terminal.

AFElement.Name: Company
AFElement.Description: A company is a legal entity that owns and operates power system resources and is a party to interchange and transmission contracts.

AFElement.Name: CompositeSwitch
AFElement.Description: A model of a set of individual Switches normally enclosed within the same cabinet and possibly with interlocks that restrict the combination of switch positions. These are typically found in medium voltage distribution networks. A CompositeSwitch could represent a Ring-Main-Unit (RMU), or pad-mounted switchgear, with primitive internal devices such as an internal bus-bar plus 3 or 4 internal switches each of which may individually be open or closed. A CompositeSwitch and a set of contained Switches can also be used to represent a multi-position switch e.g. a switch that can connect a circuit to Ground, Open or Busbar.

AFElement.Name: ConductingEquipment
AFElement.Description: The parts of the power system that are designed to carry current or that are conductively connected therewith. ConductingEquipment is contained within an EquipmentContainer that may be a Substation, or a VoltageLevel or a Bay within a Substation.

AFElement.Name: Conductor
AFElement.Description: Combination of conducting material with consistent electrical characteristics, building a single electrical system, used to carry current between points in the power system.

AFElement.Name: Connector
AFElement.Description: A conductor, or group of conductors, with negligible impedance, that serve to connect other conducting equipment within a single substation and are modelled with a single logical terminal.

AFElement.Name: Control
AFElement.Description: Control is used for supervisory/device control. It represents control outputs that are used to change the state in a process, e.g. close or open breaker, a set point value or a raise lower command.

AFElement.Name: DCLineSegment
AFElement.Description: A wire or combination of wires not insulated from one another, with consistent electrical characteristics, used to carry direct current between points in the DC region of the power system.

AFElement.Name: Disconnector
AFElement.Description: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for changing the connections in a circuit, or for isolating a circuit or equipment from a source of power. It is required to open or close circuits when negligible current is broken or made.

AFElement.Name: EnergyConsumer
AFElement.Description: Generic user of energy - a point of consumption on the power system model

AFElement.Name: Equipment
AFElement.Description: The parts of a power system that are physical devices, electronic or mechanical

AFElement.Name: EquipmentContainer
AFElement.Description: A modeling construct to provide a root class for all Equipment classes

AFElement.Name: Fuse
AFElement.Description: An overcurrent protective device with a circuit opening fusible part that is heated and severed by the passage of overcurrent through it. A fuse is considered a switching device because it breaks current.

AFElement.Name: GeographicalRegion
AFElement.Description: A geographical region of a power system network model.

AFElement.Name: Ground
AFElement.Description: A common point for connecting grounded conducting equipment such as shunt capacitors. The power system model can have more than one ground.

AFElement.Name: GroundDisconnector
AFElement.Description: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for isolating a circuit or equipment from Ground.

AFElement.Name: IdentifiedObject
AFElement.Description: This is a root class to provide common naming attributes for all classes needing naming attributes

AFElement.Name: Jumper
AFElement.Description: A short section of conductor with negligible impedance which can be manually removed and replaced if the circuit is de-energized. Note that zero-impedance branches can be modelled by an ACLineSegment with a zero impedance ConductorType

AFElement.Name: Junction
AFElement.Description: A point where one or more conducting equipments are connected with zero resistance.

AFElement.Name: Line
AFElement.Description: A component part of a system extending between adjacent substations or from a substation to an adjacent interconnection point.

AFElement.Name: LoadBreakSwitch
AFElement.Description: A mechanical switching device capable of making, carrying, and breaking currents under normal operating conditions.

AFElement.Name: Measurement
AFElement.Description: A Measurement represents any measured, calculated or non-measured non-calculated quantity. Any piece of equipment may contain Measurements, e.g. a substation may have temperature measurements and door open indications, a transformer may have oil temperature and tank pressure measurements, a bay may contain a number of power flow measurements and a Breaker may contain a switch status measurement. The PSR - Measurement association is intended to capture this use of Measurement and is included in the naming hierarchy based on EquipmentContainer. The naming hierarchy typically has Measurements as leafs, e.g. Substation-VoltageLevel-Bay-Switch-Measurement. Some Measurements represent quantities related to a particular sensor location in the network, e.g. a voltage transformer (PT) at a busbar or a current transformer (CT) at the bar between a breaker and an isolator. The sensing position is not captured in the PSR - Measurement association. Instead it is captured by the Measurement - Te

AFElement.Name: PowerSystemResource
AFElement.Description: A power system resource can be an item of equipment such as a Switch, an EquipmentContainer containing many individual items of equipment such as a Substation, or an organisational entity such as Company or SubControlArea. This provides for the nesting of collections of PowerSystemResources within other PowerSystemResources. For example, a Switch could be a member of a Substation and a Substation could be a member of a division of a Company.

AFElement.Name: PowerTransformer
AFElement.Description: An electrical device consisting of two or more coupled windings, with or without a magnetic core, for introducing mutual coupling between electric circuits. Transformers can be used to control voltage and phase shift (active power flow).

AFElement.Name: RectifierInverter
AFElement.Description: Bi-directional AC-DC conversion equipment that can be used to control DC current, DC voltage, DC power flow, or firing angle.

AFElement.Name: RegulatingCondEq
AFElement.Description: RegulatingCondEq is a type of ConductingEquipment that can regulate Measurements and have a RegulationSchedule.

AFElement.Name: SeriesCompensator
AFElement.Description: A Series Compensator is a series capacitor or reactor or an AC transmission line without charging susceptance.

AFElement.Name: ServiceDeliveryPoint
AFElement.Description: There can be multiple service points at a single ServiceLocation, each one identified as a ServiceDeliveryPoint. They deliver service in accordance with a CustomerAgreement. A service point exists within a ServiceLocation and is used at the place where a meter may be installed. Properties include: 1) serviceType (gas, electric, water) 2) servicePhase 3) voltageLevel 4) vtdtReference (optional, where meters are indirectly connected for a medium voltage service).

AFElement.Name: ShuntCompensator
AFElement.Description: A shunt capacitor or reactor or switchable bank of shunt capacitors or reactors. A section of a shunt compensator is an individual capacitor or reactor. Negative values for mVArPerSection and nominalMVAr indicate that the compensator is a reactor.

AFElement.Name: StaticVarCompensator
AFElement.Description: A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms. The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.
